Office**Job Description**


At Thermo Fisher Scientific, our Finance teams are important to our business and functional teams to make educated, sound decisions that drive our Mission and make us a stable and trusted industry leader. From Financial Planning \& Analysis, Tax, Treasury, Financial Reporting, Audit, Investor Relations, Strategy \& Corporate Development to Accounting, our Finance functions have a diverse and global presence, providing significant opportunities to develop outstanding career experiences and perspectives.  



**How you will make an impact:**  



The Italian Subsidiary of the Protein Diagnostics Division of Thermo Fisher, offers medical devices to all the Italian main Hospitals.  



If you have a passion for financial accuracy and timeliness across a global, multi\-faceted organization, Thermo Fisher Scientific’s Accounting and Controllership function is the team for you. With a keen understanding of laws, regulations and compliance as well as reporting requirements consistent with ITA GAAP, this team uses innovative financial systems and controls, data security and robust processes to protect the company’s assets and support its short\- and long\-term growth on a global scale. From technical accounting to budgeting and forecasting to planning and reporting, you will build relationships with internal and external audit teams as well as key business partners to drive sophisticated business decisions. You will have an opportunity to build strong organizational alliances to understand and mitigate risk, as well as capture opportunities and provide valuable support to all business partners.  



Seeking a **proficient finance team member** who will provide finance, accounting and compliance to the Italian business. The successful candidate will implement accounting, controls and compliance procedures to ensure timely and accurate financial reporting. In addition, the position holder will identify and recommend operational improvement opportunities, and support leadership in achieving of business objectives.  



**What you will do**:

* Monthly and year end accounting vouchers, closing activities including journal entries, accruals, reporting and analysis;
* Management of monthly VAT registers, VAT quarterly declaration data (LIPE), and VAT annual declaration data;
* Fixed Assets monthly updates, depreciation and scrapping;
* Analysis of customers collections for the bank update and the monthly collections report;
* Balance Sheet Reconciliations;
* Withholding Tax Calculation and Certifications;
* Statutory and tax compliance activities;
* Management and printing of Statutory Accounting Registers;
* Carry out sophisticated accounting treatment and prepares financial documents and supplementary reporting
* Ensure compliance with company policy, approval authority matrix and standard operating procedure; recommends changes to strengthen control environment
* Drive continuous improvement and uses systems to increase controls and efficiencies
* Perform local taxes calculations;
* FOC Reports analysis and issue of the monthly Self invoices;
* External Agents commission calculation and related communications (Sales Target, Enasarco and FIRR);
* Control of the payment lists:
* Draft calculation of year end corporate taxes;
* Support to the External TAX Consultants for the Statutory Report and the Annual TAX Declarations;
* Support to the external Auditor for quarter and year end data;
* Administrative support to the Italian Subsidiary;
* Other activities related to the role.

 **Requirements:**

* A bachelor's degree is preferred, along with 5–10 years of experience in accounting and tax.
* Excellent understanding of financial accounting standards and internal controls.
* Excellent user of Excel and PowerPoint
* experience with IFS ERP (or equivalent) is a plus.
* Proficient verbal and written communication skills (Italian and English).

 **Travel requirements:**

* Domestic/international travel required rarely

**Location** Milan, Lombardy, Italy **Job ID** R\-255881 **Date posted** 19/07/2026

**Job Title: AI Translator \& Digital Health Lead**


**Introduction to role**:Are you ready to turn AI and Digital Health ideas into scaled solutions that deliver measurable value for patients and the business? Do you thrive at the intersection of business, data and technology, orchestrating diverse teams to move from concept to impact with pace and precision?


In this senior role, you will help shape and execute the AI and Digital Health strategy across key brands and customer journeys, translating business needs into deployable solutions and integrating them into omnichannel ecosystems. Your leadership will convert prioritized use cases into outcomes that matter: better experiences, faster decisions, stronger performance and compliant\-by\-design operations. You will align squads around clear goals, standardize data for unified measurement, and coach teams to build AI fluency—accelerating how medicines reach people who need them.


**Accountabilities**:\- Roadmap Co\-Leadership: Co\-lead the execution of the AI and Digital Health roadmap, ensuring alignment with strategic priorities and business goals;\- Use Case Delivery: Oversee end\-to\-end delivery of prioritized AI and Digital Health use cases, from ideation through pilot to scale;\- Business Translation: Translate business needs into AI\- and Digital Health–enabled solutions, coordinating with data scientists, IT and external partners to deliver value;\- Customer Journey Integration: Drive integration of AI and Digital Health solutions (medical devices, DTx and more) into key customer journeys and omnichannel ecosystems;\- Digital Asset Governance: Supervise governance of digital assets (websites, apps, social, platforms) to ensure performance, UX, accessibility and brand consistency;\- Data Standardisation: Enable standardisation of data models across web, social and CRM for unified measurement, reporting and optimisation;\- Personalisation Enablement: Support implementation of personalisation strategies across CRM and digital platforms to increase relevance and outcomes;\- Cross\-Functional Squad Leadership: Lead squads spanning Marketing, Medical, Market Access, External Communications, IT and Customer Engagement, driving execution excellence;\- Performance Management: Monitor initiative performance via KPIs, dashboards and ROI tracking, and act decisively on insights;\- Capability Building: Coach and mentor Managers and Designers, fostering AI fluency and digital capabilities across the team;\- Global Collaboration: Serve as a key interface with global teams, localising solutions and sharing best practices to scale what works;\- Compliance\-by\-Design: Ensure compliance\-by\-design across all initiatives (AI Act, GDPR, MDR) in close partnership with Legal, Compliance and Medical.


**Essential Skills/Experience**:\- 5–8\+ years of experience in Digital, Digital Marketing, AI or Digital Health roles in regulated industries;\- Proven track record in delivering digital/AI projects at scale;\- Proven track record in developing web and social media projects, SEO \& GEO strategy, digital media buying;\- Strong understanding of ecosystem such as CRM, CMS, new channels, analytics, personalization tools;\- Experience working with AI use cases (LLMs, RAG, automation, AI agents, classification, recommendation systems);\- Ability to identify and prioritize high\-impact AI use cases and build business cases (ROI\-driven);\- Solid knowledge of data governance, privacy and compliance;\- Strong program management and stakeholder management skills;\- Experience coordinating cross\-functional teams and external vendors;\- AI translation capability;\- Execution excellence and delivery mindset;\- Stakeholder influence and alignment;\- Data\-driven decision making;\- Coaching and team development;\- Fluent in Italian and English;


**Desirable Skills/Experience**:\- Advanced Degree (MBA);\- Agile working certification (PSM, PSPO, etc.);\- Experience in scaling digital \& AI solutions across markets, business units or geographies;\- Human center design experience;\- Familiarity with advanced AI topics such as model evaluation, guardrails, explainability and bias mitigation;\- Passionate about continuous learning in the AI field, with an entrepreneurial approach to innovation and problem\-solving;\- Strong leadership presence with the ability to influence senior stakeholders;\- Knowledge of interoperability standards in healthcare;\- Familiarity with cybersecurity and risk management principles applied to digital health solutions;


**Why AstraZeneca**:Here, technology is a force\-multiplier for real\-world impact—helping us get medicines to patients faster, more affordably and with greater sustainability. We embed digital capabilities end to end, from automated workflows and smart production to data\-driven decisions and machine learning that improves quality and speed. You will join a diverse, multi\-generational community that prizes curiosity, shares learnings and scales winning ideas quickly. Expect unexpected teams in the same room unleashing bold thinking, with leaders who invest in modern tools and back you to push boundaries. We value kindness alongside ambition, and we connect your contribution directly to outcomes that matter for people, society and the planet.


**Call to Action**:Step into a role where your AI leadership will turn bold ideas into scaled digital health outcomes—share your CV and show us how you will deliver impact.


